Hey there kids!

I am not online much these days, since there's plenty to do at work.. and plenty to do for school, and plenty to do with friends, and plenty to do around the house.. and soon plenty to do outdoors.

So, I live in the land of plenty, which means I have the opposite-of-plenty time for online posts.

But, I still wanted to say HEY!

Love ya!
A lot of this journal will now be friends only... I can find anything on the Internets...

I am baffled (again) at the wackiness of LJ userpics.

They come, they go. 
I am unpaid since I'm not here as much, but I can't get the userpics I want to be active.
I guess I have to delete all of them and upload the ones I want.

Sigh.

I have no time for this.

I am so happy that America gave me the birthday present I asked for!!

A President named Obama!

It's the perfect gift, that keeps on giving!!!!


Now, can I have some damn marriage?  WTF.
. . Oh yes, I am lame! I missed Bohostar's birthday! I make up for it with this: Happy berfday, Boho!

People...

Any one know of a good site hosting service that allows you to customize your content and upload your own HTML code?

I signed up for a site through this hosting service, only to realize that they give you 11 cookie cutter page templates to choose from. If I want to change a dimension of a logo space, or select a pretty shade of green, I have to PAY EXTRA EVERY MONTH. I get only a squashed area for my logo, and a shitty shade of green.

I don't want to pay extra for working more. I want a cheap host with a domain registration that allows me to code/edit the HTML any fucking way I want.

OMG.

I'm so livid. I sent an e-mail, hoping they'll refund the money. Can you only edit your HTML in the sucky, pop-up-laden, ad-banner-ridden free sites???

HELP.

.

I like to do things full on, hard-core.

I rock righteously, and mightily.

This is why I celebrate New Year's Eve by PUKING MY BRAINS OUT!!*



*Not from too much alcohol, but from a stomach virus. 


2008 better be an ass-load better than how it began.
Ugh.

Happy New Year's, everybody! 
I love  ya!

<lj user="Jewelry_Girl"> and I are fine.
We had been at the beach until 8:30 pm, and were oblivious to the tragedy until we arrived home to dozens of calls on our cell phones. (Sorry for worrying you, family!)

JG's uncles and cousin who are local firefighters are fine.
Everyone we know is (so far) fine.

It is horrifying.
CNN has actual video footage. It makes your blood run cold.

I'm very glad that my friends who take that route were not there for various and lucky reasons.

 
No words.

If you're moved to, please ...SIGN the petition... From MoveOn.org: As you may have heard, Nancy Pelosi is hoping to start off big with her "100 Hours Agenda." It's a bunch of progressive proposals, including cutting oil subsidies to invest in clean energy, getting cheaper prescription drugs for seniors, and raising the minimum wage. Naturally, the big drug companies, oil companies, and business lobbies are fighting hard to stop her. MoveOn has started a petition to Congress so we can show our representatives we're ready for some real progress, and they should act quickly to pass the 100 Hours Agenda. Plus, the total signature count and some of our comments will be read out loud on the floor of Congress during the debate -- so the more we get, the louder our voice will be.

We're FINALLY getting some snow!

We've had absolutely zip so far this year, which has been breaking all kinds of records and putting the lakes and rivers way behind schedule for next spring... but no more.

There are HUGE fluffy wet snow-gobs plummeting to the ground in massive waves.

The flock of geese that took up residence on the workplace lawn are looking really PISSED.

Hee!!!

What a mess, but it's PRETTY!

You are The Empress

Beauty, happiness, pleasure, success, luxury, dissipation.

The Empress is associated with Venus, the feminine planet, so it represents, beauty, charm, pleasure, luxury, and delight. You may be good at home decorating, art or anything to do with making things beautiful.

The Empress is a creator, be it creation of life, of romance, of art or business. While the Magician is the primal spark, the idea made real, and the High Priestess is the one who gives the idea a form, the Empress is the womb where it gestates and grows till it is ready to be born. This is why her symbol is Venus, goddess of beautiful things as well as love. Even so, the Empress is more Demeter, goddess of abundance, then sensual Venus. She is the giver of Earthly gifts, yet at the same time, she can, in anger withhold, as Demeter did when her daughter, Persephone, was kidnapped. In fury and grief, she kept the Earth barren till her child was returned to her.

HAR! My cube-mate at work cracks me up. He was explaining a recent complaint from a customer in which they said that they thought if they stopped using the credit card, they wouldn't have to make payments or be charged late fees. Then he said... "Lady, this is your credit card agreement. It has lots of words. These things, words... when you bunch them together, they make sentences. Sentences tell you things, sometimes very important things. You should try looking at the sentences on your credit card agreement..." I was laughing so hard, I couldn't breathe. We get some real idiots writing to us. (*rolls eyes*)
